  "prompt": "I haven't started CAT preparation. Is there any plan so that I can crack the exam in 2 months?",
  "response": "Cracking the CAT in 2 months is challenging, but not impossible with a focused and strategic approach. Here's a comprehensive plan:\n\nVerbal Ability and Reading Comprehension (VARC):\n1. Daily reading (1-2 hours)\n- Newspapers (The Hindu, economic times)\n- Magazines (Economist, Frontline)\n2. RC practice\n- Solve 2-3 passages daily\n- Focus on accuracy and speed\n3. Grammar and vocabulary\n- Study grammar rules\n- Learn 10-15 new words daily\n\nQuantitative Aptitude (QA):\n1. Basic concepts revisit\n- Arithmetic\n- Algebra\n- Geometry\n- Numbers\n2. Practice problems\n- 20-30 questions daily\n- Focus on speed and accuracy\n3. Mock tests for time management\n\nData Interpretation and Logical Reasoning (DILR):\n1. Practice sets daily\n2. Learn problem-solving techniques\n3. Focus on different set types\n\nOverall Strategy:\n- 4-5 hours daily study\n- Regular mock tests\n- Analyze performance\n- Work on weak areas\n- Last 15 days: Full mock tests\n\nRecommended Resources:\n- Arun Sharma books\n- TIME/Career Launcher material\n- Online mock tests\n\nRemember: Consistent effort and smart preparation are key!",
